    "RNNs are designed to handle sequential data and are well-suited for capturing the temporal dependencies in text.",
    "Despite their advantages in processing sequences, RNNs generally face challenges with long-term dependencies, which can impact their performance in capturing more complex sentiment patterns over extended sequences.",
    "Random Forest:The Random Forest model recorded an accuracy of 87.871%.",
    "As an ensemble learning technique, Forest combines predictions of multiple decision trees to improve overall performance and robustness.",
    "While effective, Random Forest's performance in sentiment analysis is somewhat limited compared to models that excel in handling textual data and learning contextual nuances."
